###
### community.e2e.http
### Prueba E2E del módulo de comunidad: posts, likes y comments.
### Ejecutar con la extensión "REST Client" de VS Code (Ctrl+Alt+R sobre cada bloque).
###
### Orden de ejecución:
###   0. Setup: registrar dos usuarios y hacer login con el primero.
###   1. Posts: crear, listar, obtener por id, validaciones.
###   2. Likes: dar like, verificar idempotencia, quitar like.
###   3. Comments: crear, listar, validaciones.
###   4. Interacción cruzada: segundo usuario da like y comenta.
###   5. Teardown: verificar estado final y health.
###

# ─── Variables globales ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@baseUrl    = http://localhost:3000
@email1     = e2e_community1@example.com
@password1  = Test1234!
@email2     = e2e_community2@example.com
@password2  = Test1234!


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BLOQUE 0 — SETUP: registro y login de dos usuarios
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 0.1 Registrar usuario 1 (autor de posts)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "E2E Community User1",
  "email": "{{email1}}",
  "password": "{{password1}}"
}

###

### 0.2 Registrar usuario 2 (lector/comentador)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "E2E Community User2",
  "email": "{{email2}}",
  "password": "{{password2}}"
}

###

### 0.3 Login usuario 1
# @name loginUser1
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email1}}",
  "password": "{{password1}}"
}

###

@token1 = {{loginUser1.body.token}}

### 0.4 Login usuario 2
# @name loginUser2
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "{{email2}}",
  "password": "{{password2}}"
}

###

@token2 = {{loginUser2.body.token}}


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BLOQUE 1 — POSTS CRUD
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1.1 GET /community — feed vacío al inicio
# Esperado: 200 { posts: [], total: 0 } o similar
GET {{baseUrl}}/community
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 1.2 POST /community — crear post de texto (sin imagen)
# Esperado: 201 con id, authorId, likesCount=0, commentsCount=0
# @name createPost1
POST {{baseUrl}}/community
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Mi primera planta en flor",
  "content": "Hoy mi monstera ha sacado su primera hoja fenestrada. Llevaba 6 meses esperando este momento. ¡La paciencia da sus frutos!",
  "tags": ["monstera", "interior", "logro"],
  "imageUrl": null
}

###

@postId1 = {{createPost1.body.id}}

### 1.3 POST /community — validación: content vacío
# Esperado: 422 VALIDATION_ERROR
POST {{baseUrl}}/community
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Post inválido",
  "content": "",
  "tags": []
}

###

### 1.4 POST /community — crear segundo post (con imageUrl)
# @name createPost2
POST {{baseUrl}}/community
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Consejo de riego para cactus",
  "content": "Los cactus en invierno necesitan riego mínimo: una vez al mes es suficiente. En verano, cada 2 semanas con sustrato bien drenado.",
  "tags": ["cactus", "riego", "consejo"],
  "imageUrl": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1459411552884-841db9b3cc2a?w=800"
}

###

@postId2 = {{createPost2.body.id}}

### 1.5 GET /community — feed con 2 posts (paginado)
# Esperado: 200 con array de 2 posts, ordenados por fecha desc
GET {{baseUrl}}/community
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 1.6 GET /community — paginación: página 2 (vacía)
# Esperado: 200 con array vacío
GET {{baseUrl}}/community?page=2&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 1.7 GET /community/:id — obtener post 1 por id
# Esperado: 200 con datos completos del post
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 1.8 GET /community/:id — id inexistente
# Esperado: 404 NOT_FOUND
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/000000000000000000000000
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 1.9 GET /community — sin token
# Esperado: 401 UNAUTHORIZED
GET {{baseUrl}}/community

###


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BLOQUE 2 — LIKES
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2.1 POST /community/:id/like — dar like al post 1 (usuario 1)
# Esperado: 200 con likesCount=1
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 2.2 POST /community/:id/like — idempotencia: dar like otra vez (mismo usuario)
# Esperado: 200 con likesCount=1 (sin duplicado)
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 2.3 GET /community/:id — verificar likesCount=1
# Esperado: 200 con likesCount: 1
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 2.4 POST /community/:id/like — usuario 2 da like al post 1
# Esperado: 200 con likesCount=2
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token2}}

###

### 2.5 GET /community/:id — verificar likesCount=2
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 2.6 DELETE /community/:id/like — usuario 1 quita su like
# Esperado: 200 con likesCount=1
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 2.7 DELETE /community/:id/like — idempotencia: quitar like que no existe
# Esperado: 200 con likesCount=1 (sin error)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 2.8 GET /community/:id — verificar likesCount=1 (solo queda like de user2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BLOQUE 3 — COMMENTS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3.1 GET /community/:id/comments — comentarios vacíos al inicio
# Esperado: 200 { comments: [], total: 0 }
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 3.2 POST /community/:id/comments — usuario 1 comenta su propio post
# Esperado: 201 con id, authorId, content
# @name createComment1
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "¡Gracias a todos por el apoyo! Ha sido un proceso de mucha paciencia."
}

###

@commentId1 = {{createComment1.body.id}}

### 3.3 POST /community/:id/comments — usuario 2 comenta
# @name createComment2
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token2}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Qué bonito! ¿Con qué sustrato la tienes? Yo tengo la mía en tierra universal y no fenestra."
}

###

@commentId2 = {{createComment2.body.id}}

### 3.4 POST /community/:id/comments — validación: comment vacío
# Esperado: 422 VALIDATION_ERROR
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": ""
}

###

### 3.5 GET /community/:id/comments — listar 2 comentarios
# Esperado: 200 con array de 2 comentarios ordenados por fecha
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

### 3.6 GET /community/:id — verificar commentsCount=2 en el post
GET {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId1}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BLOQUE 4 — INTERACCIÓN POST 2
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 4.1 POST /community/:id/like — usuarios 1 y 2 dan like al post 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId2}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###

POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId2}}/like
Authorization: Bearer {{token2}}

###

### 4.2 POST /community/:id/comments — usuario 2 comenta post 2
POST {{baseUrl}}/community/{{postId2}}/comments
Authorization: Bearer {{token2}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Muy buen consejo, lo aplicaré este invierno."
}

###

### 4.3 GET /community — feed completo con contadores actualizados
# Esperado: 200 con post1 (1 like, 2 comments) y post2 (2 likes, 1 comment)
GET {{baseUrl}}/community
Authorization: Bearer {{token1}}

###


# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BLOQUE 5 — HEALTH CHECKS
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5.1 GET /health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### 5.2 GET /ready
GET {{baseUrl}}/ready

###
